; fs-list-heap-phase-band.fk — proof that fs_list answers the DIRECTORY, not
; the heap's allocation history.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk
;
; The defect this band pins (2026-07-16, runtime/fkwu-uni.c tag 132): fs_list
; built its list with no melt trigger and, at the heap wall, returned the
; PARTIAL listing silently — so the same call answered 886 or 600 depending on
; how much unrelated allocation had happened first (one read_file was enough to
; move it). Downstream, observe/autopoietic-pulse.fk's ap-stable? read 0 on a
; freshly tended portrait: the drift detector lied, because the body's own
; directory reads depended on heap phase. See
; receipts/2026-07-16-pulse-count-invariance.md.
;
; The band is PROPERTY-shaped, not count-shaped: it never asserts what
; form/form-stdlib holds (that number grows with the body); it asserts the
; listing is EQUAL across five heap phases. Each un-bound fs_list call parks
; ~900 dead cells without any melt on the pre-healing runtime, so by the
; fourth call the build crosses the old wall and truncates — the equality
; bits fail there. On the healed runtime the 90%-melt fires mid-build with
; the accumulator rooted, and every phase answers alike. A floor guard
; (n1 > 500) keeps the phase test honest: a small directory would never
; reach the wall and the equalities would pass vacuously.
;
; run: cat form/form-stdlib/core.fk \
;          form/form-stdlib/tests/fs-list-heap-phase-band.fk > /tmp/flhp.fk
;      ./fkwu --src /tmp/flhp.fk    ; -> 31
;
; Verdict 31 when every assertion holds.

(do
    (defn flhpb-score (ok bit) (if ok bit 0))
    (defn fs-list-heap-phase-band ()
        (do
            (let n1 (len (fs_list "form/form-stdlib")))
            (let n2 (len (fs_list "form/form-stdlib")))
            (let n3 (len (fs_list "form/form-stdlib")))
            (let n4 (len (fs_list "form/form-stdlib")))
            (let n5 (len (fs_list "form/form-stdlib")))
            (let c0 (flhpb-score (gt n1 500) 1))
            (let c1 (flhpb-score (eq n1 n2) 2))
            (let c2 (flhpb-score (eq n1 n3) 4))
            (let c3 (flhpb-score (eq n1 n4) 8))
            (let c4 (flhpb-score (eq n1 n5) 16))
            (add c0 (add c1 (add c2 (add c3 c4))))))
    (fs-list-heap-phase-band))
